This is a derangement problem. I need to find the probability that none of the 12 students roll their own number.

The number of derangements of n items is given by:
$$D_n = n! \sum_{i=0}^{n} \frac{(-1)^i}{i!}$$

For n = 12:
$$D_{12} = 12! \sum_{i=0}^{12} \frac{(-1)^i}{i!}$$

The total number of possible outcomes when 12 students each roll a 12-sided die is $12^{12}$.

The number of ways to have no matches is $D_{12}$.

