- Condition: x/(1-x) ≥ 2
- This gives: x ≥ 2(1-x)
- Therefore: x ≥ 2 - 2x
- So: 3x ≥ 2
- Therefore: x ≥ 2/3

The favorable outcomes are:
- x ∈ [0, 1/3] with length 1/3
- x ∈ [2/3, 1] with length 1/3

Total favorable length: 1/3 + 1/3 = 2/3

Probability = (2/3)/1 = 2/3 ≈ 0.667

