3. P(PT) = P(C) + 0.16 (PT exceeds C by 16%)

**Setting up equations:**

From the complement rule:
P(PT ∪ C) = 1 - P(neither) = 1 - 0.08 = 0.92

Using the inclusion-exclusion principle:
P(PT ∪ C) = P(PT) + P(C) - P(PT ∩ C)

Substituting known values:
0.92 = P(PT) + P(C) - 0.28
P(PT) + P(C) = 1.20

